window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>This set contains <i>Mine </i>and <i>His</i>, the complete Ties That Bind Duet! </p> <p><b><i>Mine</i></b><i> </i></p> <p>She was never supposed to walk into my club. But she did. </p> <p>I shouldn’t have looked twice at her. But I did. </p> <p>The criminal underworld is no place for a girl like her. </p> <p>One night with Katerina isn’t enough, but men like me can’t afford to be weak. So I tell her to leave me behind. </p> <p>She does, but not before she sees something she shouldn’t. </p> <p>When she goes into hiding, it’s my duty to hunt her down. I have a job to do, and she needs to disappear for good. </p> <p>But four years later, Kat isn’t alone anymore. And the little boy right beside her looks just like me. </p> <p><b><i>His</i></b><i> </i></p> <p>I’ve been in hiding for four years. On the run from the man in whose bed I once slept. </p> <p>I saw something I shouldn’t have seen. Took something I shouldn’t have taken. </p> <p>And he’s just found me. </p> <p>But it’s not just my safety I have to worry about. I have a little boy. <i>His</i> little boy. The secret baby of a Russian mobster. </p> <p>He told me in no uncertain terms that I’m his. That we would be a family. </p> <p>But his uncle still wants me dead, and I know the man who’s been hunting me is the only one who can keep us safe. </p>"; 
